Listen up 🗣️ One thing I recently can't live without are my Mugsy Jeans. True story! I’ve literally been wearing them any chance I get, including my 21+ hour travel day to Australia. Mugsy makes the most comfortable jeans, chinos, and cords I own. If y’all are looking for that perfect gift for that person in your life, check out mugsyjeans.com and use my code Austen10 to save 10% on your order 🎅🏼 🎄
A nice little collaborative effort here for Sunday Gospel Brunch! Now that my folks have retired, my mother commented that she’s never been/always wanted to come 🥂

Can’t believe it’s already been a week since the grand opening of @carriagehousenyc !! I’m admittedly terrible at posting on social media sometimes, but this one deserves to be highlighted, if not for the sole purpose of giving a massive shoutout to @fork_knife @philtestanyc @cesarx.garcia and countless others, who have put their blood sweat and tears into opening this restaurant.
And not just opening the restaurant, but ensuring everything was executed to the highest standard for our friends, family and patrons!

To say the evening exceeded all expectations would be an understatement!

Go on Tock, or chnyc.com, to make your reservations, and see what this incredible team has put together for your next night out !

Food Pictured, in order:
- Seasonal Butter Candle
- Tuna, salmon, scallop steak and mushroom Pomme Pave bites
- Uni Butter Tagliatelle
- Peri Peri Bird 1/2 Chicken
- Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Casserole

Also, great time getting to follow my guy @keeganbradley1 around the course, can’t wait til next year, Heritage ! ⛳️ 😎
Still cheesin thinkin back to getting ‘Coronated’ in my hometown at the @charlottefc game this past weekend! Thank you to everyone who made it possible! #forthecrown

Pinching myself that I’m getting to play @golfkohler with some of my best mates on this beautiful 4th of July. Happy 4th y’all! 🇺🇸

I’m looking back at pictures as the dust finally settles from one heck of a 🪣 list golf trip with a one heck of a crew!

Huge thanks to www.WisconsinGetaways.com @wisconsingetaways for letting us use this dream Castle Vineyard as our home base! If you’re looking for a sign to play Whistling Straits, or book a loved ones trip…this is it. Use code ‘WHISTLINGWG’ for a special discount off your booking!

The Kroll’s have much to celebrate. 5 weeks ago, the fam was preparing for our much anticipated Italian vacation which had been on the calendar for more than 4 months. 10 days prior to our trip, dads health came into question. Suffice to say, we cancelled the trip, with the ‘light at the end of the tunnel’ hope, that we’d be able to reschedule and eventually raise a glass together (I assure you it wasn’t just my glass raised 😅) and cheers!

Well… today is that day ! Here we are, together in Rome. Drinking, laughing, poking fun (my new bucket hat has already come under fire) 
Life is good. We are lucky. We are happy 🇮🇹 🇫🇷
Todays forecast: drinking Rose in Saint-Tropez

@pillowsnbeer is back for season 4, and better than ever (2x a week better, to be exact)
Check out our brand new website PillowsandBeer.com to purchase merch from our last tour, and to find all the latest happenings with the podcast, as well as our upcoming tour !

We married off another Kroll this weekend! Congratulations to Haley and Jake, and thank you for ‘making’ us come to Colorado. Nothing like a summer wedding in the mountains!

Fun little tidbit: my dads brother has two daughters. Both married, and no longer Kroll’s. I have a sister (well 2). And when Katie gets married… Welp, i’m the last hope to keep the Kroll lineage alive! 
No pressure 😅

Holy shit y’all! This is the 6th time i’m posting one of these ! And since I neverr post stuff like this, I figured today was as good a day as any to start.
Season 9 is a doozy- full of high ups and trench-like-downs. For me, personally, this season is a long journey, full of growth… Hard truths, learning moments, laughter, crying (even ugly crying) and at times, even regression. 
Old Friendships were tested, and some were even strengthened. 

I choose year in and year out to show every aspect of my life, in the raw. That means the good, the bad, the really bad , the fun, and the funny. Every year, without fail, I find myself anxious and excited for everyone to see what we were able to capture…and this year is no different. 

Season 9 is layered and complex, and that’s quite simply because we put our lives out there for the world to see. And I can’t believe I’m saying this, but I can’t wait to share it with you 🍻 
Catch Southern Charm Season 9 premiere at 9 pm EST on @bravotv

First live show of @pillowsnbeer second tour is RIGHT. AROUND. THE CORNER !! Who’s joining us for round 2!? 👯‍♂️🕺🏼
